# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sporeus weekly self-audit — host crontab snippet
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What this is:
#   A no-cost, no-LLM, no-network audit that grep/finds across the repo and
#   produces a markdown report at audit-reports/audit-YYYY-MM-DD.md.
#
# How to install (host cron):
#   1. Open your user crontab:
#        crontab -e
#   2. Append the line below (uncomment first), adjusting the path if your
#      checkout lives somewhere other than /home/hlnx4/sporeus-athlete-app.
#   3. Save & exit. cron will pick it up automatically — no daemon restart.
#
# How to verify it ran:
#   tail /tmp/sporeus-audit.log
#   ls -lt /home/hlnx4/sporeus-athlete-app/audit-reports/ | head
#
# How to disable:
#   crontab -e   # then delete the line
#   # OR (nuclear) crontab -r   # removes ALL of your cron entries — use with care
#
# Notes:
#   - cron uses the user's local timezone (run `date` to confirm).
#   - The script never calls an LLM, never pushes to git, never hits the network.
#   - Reports are kept under audit-reports/ which is gitignored — stale reports
#     accumulate locally; prune them manually if disk pressure becomes an issue.
#   - Runtime budget: < 60 seconds. If yours runs longer, file an issue.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Sporeus weekly audit — runs every Monday 9:07am local time
7 9 * * 1 cd /home/hlnx4/sporeus-athlete-app && ./scripts/weekly-audit.sh > /tmp/sporeus-audit.log 2>&1
